.

dt(0, df=3)
## [1] 0.3675526
pt(0, df=3)
## [1] 0.5
qt(0.5, df=3)
## [1] 0
rt(10, df=3)
##  [1] -0.7129326  1.0520925  0.6214144 -0.8911455 -0.3603646  1.0689039
##  [7]  5.9042515 -1.5465802  1.2604398  0.5360064
x <- seq(from = -4 , to = 4 , length = 1000)
yn <- dt(x , df=3)
yn2 <- dt(x , df=30)
plot(x, yn , ylab="y", main="t-distribution",type="l", ylim=c(0, 0.5))
lines(x, yn2,col="red")
lines(x, dnorm(x,mean=0,sd=1), col="blue")
